  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Possible prison time (typically 5-20 years)\n- Substantial financial penalties and fines\n\n2. Asset seizure\n- Government can confiscate money and assets related to the crime\n- Potential forfeiture of property gained through illegal means\n\n3. Civil penalties\n- Additional financial sanctions\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\n4. Professional consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential business/professional reputation damage\n\nSpecific penalties depend on:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Frequency of the offense\n- Individual's criminal history\n- Specific circumstances of the case\n\nThe exact legal process and consequences can vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is generally considered a serious financial crime with significant legal ramifications.",
